05/01/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov and Foreign Minister Solomon Passy met Saturday (4 January) to discuss the country's foreign policy priorities for this year.
Passy, who initiated the meeting, said that 2003 would be very important in view of Bulgaria's NATO accession.
They agreed there would be no significant ambassadorial changes before membership negotiations are finalised.
Parvanov decided to call a meeting of the National Security Consultative Council on 9 January, dedicated to Bulgaria's readiness to enter the alliance.
(Sega, BTA, news.bg - 04/01/03;
Mediapool - 03/01/03)
